- No fuss entry level monitor with a hdmi cable included. Good for plug and play.
- Color reproduction is okay for entry level

What is isn't good
- The marketing hype around thin bezels is misplaced. The bezels are as big as they used to come in 2010s.
- The viewing angle is severely limited. Works when you right in front of the monitor but not you view from obtuse angle. Should be expected from a VA screen. This is not an IPS screen. But the dell website claims 178 degrees viewing angle.
- Comes with default 16A power adapter, the ones used for geysers and heavy appliances."
