264,4.4 out of 5,"The stand is good for my quad monitor setup of 27"". It's sturdy. But the base is not heavy. It's hollow from bottom side. So if you fit a screen on one arm it topples on that side till you add another screen on other arm. Also the arms resting in air so there are problem in symmetricity along the arm length. For my setup left arm level is slightly (4-5mm) lower than right arm. So the screens are not fitting with corner to corner perfectly. If this does not bother you, you may consider 5/5 points for finishing and sturdiness."
