419,4.5 out of 5,"Product description: ***** Received as described
Installation: **** Medium Efforts(easy)
Build quality : ***** Very Good

Value for money : *****(bought it for 6960 ₹)

Box contains:
✔️ 2 gas spring arms
✔️ Vesa mount pattern 75mm & 100mm
✔️ 1 base clamp
✔️ 1 base pillar
✔️ lots of screws and 2 Allen keys

The good:
➕ Easy gas spring adjustment
➕ Integrated cable management
➕ Dual installation options C clamp/grommet mount
➕ Dual motion full monitor
➕ Vesa pattern options 75mm/100mm

The bad:
➖ little bit costly (but have gas springs)

Assembly was fairly straight forward. I had it installed within 15 minutes.

First, take it out of the box, the arms are tied down with a tie wrap. As soon as you cut it, the arms will extend, so make sure that you hold the arm and the base is against something. There is a caution sticker attached with instructions.

The arms are sturdy and stay in place when I move the monitors. Their range of motion is also really impressive, allowing me to perfectly line up the two screens despite them being different brands. Also, the all-black construction looks so much better than a lot of other models.

The base itself was a lot bigger then I expected and did look a lot sturdier as it covered a wider surface area.

I used the clamp that however clamp was not able to accommodate the thickness of my desk so compensated with the chunks of boards.

I have 2x 25"" curve screens and 2x old 16"" flat screens. Vesa installation can be used but my monitors were not VESA compatible so I ordered non-VESA mount adapters to accommodate 16"" AOC old monitors. It worked like charm. Max screen size that arms could accommodate is 29"" weighing 8 kg each.

Rotation:
 • Arm joint attached to pillar = 135°
 • Mid arm joint = 180°
 • Vesa joint with arm = 90°
 • Vesa and monitor = 180°

Very impressed by the range of motion that I was able to get out of it and was easy to move with the gas springs.

Even gas spring tension can be adjusted according to your requirements.

Very solid, versatile, easy to assemble with clear directions, air-pistons fully functional and adjustable.

I was impressed with how much space I saved and how neat the whole thing looked!

All in all, I am totally happy with the item, the price, and the vendor. I would highly recommend it."
