471,4.4 out of 5,"The monitor is perfect for productivity, media consumption and casual gaming. Brightness is more than enough. I'm running it at just 10% brightness as I use it fairly close. Picture is sharp and crisp. While it does support HDCP, it lacks HDCP 2.2. 10 bit color is possible only in 60 Hz. It defaults to 8 bit in 75 Hz, which is a minor con. It is more than enough for 1440p gaming at 60 Hz or 75 Hz. Casual gamers need not worry. It's good enough. The stand is perfectly functional. The placement of the cable mounts and the buttons are absolutely awful. If you can look past that, just go for it."
