903,5 out of 5,"Overall an amazing screen for the price. Firstly this screen is not made for gaming but productivity. The only advantage is if you want to play games at 2k resolution. Personally I bought this screen for photo editing and coding. I was eyeing the Dell U2415. Below are some points that beat the Dell monitor.
Pros:
- Acurate color reproduction and super bright
- Solid build quality
- amazing clarity and sharpness. Only 2k monitor under 20k that produces accurate colors.
- Best pivot stand for both horizontal and vertal movement with height adjustment
- Factory calibrated as per ColorRec standards.
- Good software and setting options with color profiles
- Decent number of ports and connectivity.
- BenQ makes the best screens and overall a great IPS pannel with little back light bleeding (only in one corner)
-Decent speakers.
- solid stand with rubber grips.
- matte finish better than dell monitors
Cons:
- Thick bezels as compared to competition. Makes it less aesthetic. But who cares for that when you need an accurate monitor.
- thicker and heavier as compared to competition.
- No HDMI cable included in the box.

If you need a monitor for editing purposes, go for this one!"
