1026,4.2 out of 5,"Native Support is 120hz on 1920x1080p. You can change the settings though and go 144hz if you want on Display settings on both Nvidia and Windows Panel.
1ms Mode reduces the Brightness to Half to reduce Ghosting. Although Same as AOC 24G2. Image Quality is Top Notch as IPS Panel. Small Bezels add to Amazing View Percentage. Has Manual Image Adjustment Settings in the Monitors panel like Blue Light Filter, Black Stabilization, Advanced DCR, Response time(Standard, Advanced, UltraFast).
Tested on Both AMD and Nvidia:
AMD Freesync Premium Supported over both HDMI Ports Provided behind the Panel.
Nvidia Gsync Supported over DisplayPort provided behind the Panel.
Both are Upto 144hz.
Response time is 1MS GTG although the brightness drops to half just like AOC 24G2. But Its looks just fine for me.
Package Details: Comes with 1, 3 Pin Flat Power Connecter and 1, 3 Pin Rounded Power Connected and 1 High Quality HDMI Cable. A Cable Support Pin to Attach behind the Monitor.
The Stand Also supports a Headphone Hang Slot to hang Your Audio Peripherals.

My Verdict: Go for this If AOC 24G2 is not available is your Region. Although Both Monitor Provide almost same picture quality with features."
