1040,4 out of 5," The product was delivered on 1st April 2021 and i started having dead pixels issue on 13th April, I complained regarding that to LG customer service and they visited for review on the same day.
Their statement was there need to be more dead pixels on screen only than we can request replacement.
This is so dump, You are buying 60K monitor for editorial work and have to sit close to the monitor and every time you see dead pixels in front of your eyes.
Very poor customer service. My issue have been escalated further cause i told them no matter what i need new display. While buying how a customer knows that if in future they are having dead pixel issue there need to be 7 dead pixels for replacement? Then i would never buy it in the first place. They should mention every detail.
Also i checked their warranty policy and there is noting in written about dead pixels. So are they making us fools?
Good for you guys if you are reading this review don't buy this monitor, better go for other brand."
